1
00:00:01,293 --> 00:00:04,171
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:22,914 --> 00:01:28,797
PERFORMANCE

3
00:01:30,424 --> 00:01:33,302
[Higuchi] Hey, I thought we were supposed
to be meeting every other week,

4
00:01:33,427 --> 00:01:34,428
not this often.

5
00:01:34,678 --> 00:01:38,056
[Ooi] It can't be helped.
We just received a new report from Coil.

6
00:01:38,140 --> 00:01:41,059
He says that Misa Amane might know L.

7
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:46,857
According to Coil, L once questioned
Amane as part of his Kira investigation.

8
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:48,442
But see, here's the problem.

9
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:52,904
He says, "I've been able to deduce
that Amane worships Kira.

10
00:01:53,947 --> 00:01:57,117
At the moment, Yoshida Productions
is trying to promote Amane

11
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,869
as the new face of Yotsuba.

12
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:02,623
My recommendation is that Yotsuba use her
for the next ad campaign

13
00:02:02,706 --> 00:02:05,959
and take the opportunity
to extract information about L."

14
00:02:06,335 --> 00:02:08,003
Personally, I don't like the idea.

15
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:10,213
It's unacceptable, if you ask me.

16
00:02:10,631 --> 00:02:13,634
Oh, really?
It seems like a perfectly good plan.

17
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:16,053
[Namikawa] I don't think that's
what Ooi was trying to say.

18
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:19,431
It's supposed to be Coil's job
to investigate L's identity.

19
00:02:20,057 --> 00:02:23,602
It doesn't make sense for him to leave
all the hard work to us, in my opinion.

20
00:02:24,353 --> 00:02:27,939
Exactly. We're paying him
to uncover L's identity, after all.

21
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:31,401
Why don't we contact Coil
and see what he has to say?

22
00:02:32,194 --> 00:02:33,904
[Namikawa] Yes, that's a good idea.

23
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:40,202
Mr. Kida, I thought we agreed before
that you'd only call me if it was urgent.

24
00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:41,578
So, is it an emergency?

25
00:02:44,206 --> 00:02:45,415
Yes, I understand.

26
00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:48,585
In that case, I think I have
an even better idea.

27
00:02:51,046 --> 00:02:52,881
[Higuchi] Even after
those meetings are over,

28
00:02:52,964 --> 00:02:54,883
I have to come home to punish criminals.

29
00:02:55,342 --> 00:02:57,511
Being Kira is so time-consuming,

30
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:00,764
but things sure have become
more interesting lately.

31
00:03:01,306 --> 00:03:04,476
It's pretty clear that Misa Amane
is the Second Kira,

32
00:03:04,643 --> 00:03:06,603
and that L must have
caught her at some point.

33
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:10,065
The only way she could have
gotten out of that situation

34
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:12,317
is by forfeiting ownership
of her Death Note

35
00:03:12,401 --> 00:03:14,653
and losing all memories
of what she did with it.

36
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:18,115
I'm not about to leave things as they are.

37
00:03:19,157 --> 00:03:21,952
I'm going to make Misa Amane my wife.

38
00:03:22,035 --> 00:03:22,911
Huh?

39
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:27,916
[laughs]

40
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:30,335
Everything I could ever want.

41
00:03:30,711 --> 00:03:33,380
Money, power, and a beautiful wife.

42
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:36,049
That'll be enough to make anyone envious.

43
00:03:37,676 --> 00:03:42,514
Once we're married, I'll just invest
a large lump sum in her life insurance.

44
00:03:43,432 --> 00:03:46,184
[Rem] She would never marry
such a disgusting fool.

45
00:03:47,436 --> 00:03:51,148
Rem, make sure you hide the notebook
in the usual place.

46
00:04:00,365 --> 00:04:03,034
Right now, this is the only thing I can do

47
00:04:03,285 --> 00:04:04,703
for Misa's sake.

48
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:11,209
[L] All right!
Let's try again, from the top.

49
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:12,753
Tell me, Misa...

50
00:04:12,836 --> 00:04:15,589
Is it true you once said that you came
to Tokyo in order to meet Ki--

51
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:17,257
-What?
-[L groans]

52
00:04:17,841 --> 00:04:20,010
Misa, please stop overacting.

53
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:22,262
It looks too cheesy, not to mention fake.

54
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:25,182
Huh? But I thought
that was a realistic performance.

55
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:26,558
[L] Just do it again.

56
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:29,352
Whatever you say, oh, so great director...

57
00:04:29,436 --> 00:04:31,772
[L] If you don't get serious about this,
I'll kick you.

58
00:04:31,855 --> 00:04:32,814
[Misa harrumphs]

59
00:04:35,776 --> 00:04:37,819
Uh, Misa-Misa…

60
00:04:37,944 --> 00:04:39,738
You're not smiling enough, Mochi.

61
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:41,281
And you can just call me Misa, y'know.

62
00:04:41,573 --> 00:04:45,243
I'm not cut out for this,
but it's part of my job so...

63
00:04:45,452 --> 00:04:47,287
[exhales dramatically]

64
00:04:47,829 --> 00:04:50,457
-Misa-Misa!
-What is it, Mochi?

65
00:04:50,624 --> 00:04:52,501
Today, you have an interview
with the Yotsuba Group

66
00:04:52,584 --> 00:04:54,628
to see if they'll use you
in their new ad campaign.

67
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:56,505
But remember,
this is also an infiltration mission,

68
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:57,714
so stay sharp!

69
00:04:58,256 --> 00:05:00,217
Don't you worry.
I already know about that.

70
00:05:00,592 --> 00:05:03,678
And, of course, that means
you can't let your cover fall either.

71
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:07,098
You're gonna play the character
of the hyper-energetic manager, okay?

72
00:05:07,349 --> 00:05:10,185
[Mogi] Right! Bring it on!
[cheers]

73
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:13,146
[Shimura] Sorry to keep you waiting.

74
00:05:13,647 --> 00:05:14,815
Good morning!

75
00:05:15,106 --> 00:05:18,735
I'm Misa-Misa's manager, Kanichi Moji,
also known as Mochi.

76
00:05:18,819 --> 00:05:20,529
-Mr. Ooi, Mr. Shimura.
-Pleased to meet you.

77
00:05:20,612 --> 00:05:21,905
It's so nice to see you again.

78
00:05:22,239 --> 00:05:23,782
Good luck, Misa-Misa!

79
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:26,201
[Misa] Way to go, Mochi. You're a natural!

80
00:05:26,284 --> 00:05:28,995
I'll be here ready to celebrate
when they decide to hire you!

81
00:05:32,374 --> 00:05:34,417
I don't think I'm cut out for this.

82
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:40,924
Now then, I don't believe
you and I have met before,

83
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:41,925
have we, Misa?

84
00:05:42,509 --> 00:05:43,718
My name is John Wallace.

85
00:05:43,802 --> 00:05:46,137
I'm the executive adviser
for the advertising department.

86
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:48,515
-Nice to meet you.
-Thank you.

87
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:50,100
I'm very pleased to meet you too.

88
00:05:50,642 --> 00:05:53,854
Well, this might seem a little bit sudden
but I'd like to be honest with you.

89
00:05:54,354 --> 00:05:55,647
We've been talking about it

90
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:58,400
and we've pretty much decided
to hire you already.

91
00:05:58,608 --> 00:06:01,862
But before we make it official,
we'd like to clarify a few things.

92
00:06:02,279 --> 00:06:03,280
[Misa] Yes?

93
00:06:03,738 --> 00:06:06,199
We've been doing
a little background check on you

94
00:06:06,283 --> 00:06:07,492
and according to our sources,

95
00:06:07,576 --> 00:06:09,578
a burglar killed your parents
during a robbery.

96
00:06:09,661 --> 00:06:11,746
You worship Kira
because he killed the suspect.

97
00:06:12,289 --> 00:06:16,251
Isn't it true that you came to Tokyo
in hope of finding and meeting Kira?

98
00:06:16,501 --> 00:06:17,419
[gasps]

99
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:20,630
What? Who did you hear that from?

100
00:06:20,881 --> 00:06:22,424
[Aiber] I'm afraid I can't answer that.

101
00:06:22,716 --> 00:06:25,760
The information is reliable, and now,
I'd say it's confirmed.

102
00:06:26,011 --> 00:06:28,722
The look on your face tells me
that these are the facts.

103
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:30,807
Huh?

104
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:33,935
[Ooi] Coil, I never thought
you investigated that far.

105
00:06:34,436 --> 00:06:38,315
Also, you're still hiding something
from us, aren't you?

106
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:41,234
Something you'd prefer
the world not to know.

107
00:06:46,323 --> 00:06:49,284
Okay, here's where I pause
and look nervous.

108
00:06:50,535 --> 00:06:52,662
It seems you were detained
by the detective L

109
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:54,039
for a short period of time.

110
00:06:54,456 --> 00:06:57,083
We'd like you to tell us the full story
of what really happened.

111
00:06:57,667 --> 00:07:01,254
It would be a problem if the new face
of Yotsuba turned out to be Kira.

112
00:07:01,713 --> 00:07:04,341
Yes. We would appreciate it
if you were honest with us.

113
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:07,260
All right, I understand.

114
00:07:07,928 --> 00:07:09,471
I'll tell you everything.

115
00:07:11,306 --> 00:07:13,433
[Misa] Yes, I was held for questioning.

116
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,976
I didn't think it was L,

117
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:17,604
but he did ask me lots of questions
about Kira.

118
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:22,150
But I'm not the second Kira,
and I never was.

119
00:07:22,317 --> 00:07:23,985
I was released because he realized

120
00:07:24,069 --> 00:07:26,363
I didn't have anything to do
with Kira after all.

121
00:07:26,821 --> 00:07:29,908
Did you manage to see who it was
that was restraining you?

122
00:07:30,158 --> 00:07:32,369
[Misa] No, I was blindfolded
the whole time.

123
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:35,455
But if he asked you questions,
surely you heard his voice, right?

124
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:38,124
[Misa] Only through a speaker
and voice filters, so...

125
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:39,626
Come on.

126
00:07:40,001 --> 00:07:41,378
What the hell is this anyway?

127
00:07:41,503 --> 00:07:43,672
A job interview or a police interrogation?

128
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,632
How long are we gonna keep this up?

129
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:47,050
I'm going to the bathroom.

130
00:07:47,258 --> 00:07:50,470
He has a point. It seems the interview
veered a little off track.

131
00:07:50,595 --> 00:07:51,721
We're very sorry.

132
00:07:53,682 --> 00:07:57,060
Excuse me, but would you mind
if I went to the bathroom as well?

133
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:58,645
[water flowing]

134
00:07:58,853 --> 00:08:01,314
[Misa] Oh, this is getting exhausting.

135
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:03,608
But everything's going well so far.

136
00:08:03,692 --> 00:08:05,151
I just have to keep it up.

137
00:08:09,364 --> 00:08:10,532
[Misa gasps]

138
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:16,079
Being touched by this scrap of paper alone

139
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:18,373
will not restore her memories
of the Death Note.

140
00:08:18,665 --> 00:08:21,751
But at least now,
Misa can see me once again.

141
00:08:22,585 --> 00:08:24,254
[Misa whimpers] What is this thing?

142
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:25,964
Some kind of monster?

143
00:08:26,715 --> 00:08:30,051
Misa, you're in a dangerous situation
right now.

144
00:08:30,218 --> 00:08:33,680
There are people within Yotsuba
who can easily have you killed.

145
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:35,557
I've come here to warn you.

146
00:08:36,182 --> 00:08:37,851
Calm down and listen to me.

147
00:08:38,184 --> 00:08:40,103
[Misa] Calm down? How can I?

148
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:42,188
This thing looks like it's gonna kill me.

149
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:45,358
Please, believe me, I'm your ally.

150
00:08:46,026 --> 00:08:47,777
My… ally?

151
00:08:49,821 --> 00:08:51,698
[Matsuda] Oh man,
I wonder if Misa-Misa's all right.

152
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:54,743
Maybe we should have wired her
or used something to track her movements.

153
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:56,828
[Light] Just as I thought.

154
00:08:57,162 --> 00:09:00,665
The Kira before I was detained
and the one that surfaced afterwards,

155
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:02,459
they must be two different people.

156
00:09:02,625 --> 00:09:04,294
The MO clearly doesn't match.

157
00:09:04,836 --> 00:09:06,254
This Kira is killing criminals

158
00:09:06,337 --> 00:09:08,715
as soon as they've had
their crime broadcast on TV,

159
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,508
regardless of the situation.

160
00:09:11,092 --> 00:09:13,595
He's punishing people
who never intended to kill,

161
00:09:13,928 --> 00:09:16,097
those who sincerely regretted
their crimes,

162
00:09:16,264 --> 00:09:18,558
or people with excusable circumstances.

163
00:09:18,892 --> 00:09:22,187
The original Kira would have
never punished those kinds of people.

164
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:26,274
That's the sort of distinction I'd make,
if I were him.

165
00:09:27,859 --> 00:09:33,281
The way the original Kira acted
is disturbingly close to my ideals.

166
00:09:34,908 --> 00:09:37,535
[sighs] What the hell am I thinking?

167
00:09:38,495 --> 00:09:39,871
I'm not Kira.

168
00:09:40,288 --> 00:09:41,581
Something's gotta be wrong with me

169
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:44,375
if I'm seriously comparing myself
to that murderer.

170
00:09:45,168 --> 00:09:46,711
Light Yagami is Kira.

171
00:09:46,878 --> 00:09:47,796
[Misa gasps]

172
00:09:48,546 --> 00:09:51,257
Tell me, what is Light doing
at the moment?

173
00:09:53,218 --> 00:09:54,969
[muffled speech]

174
00:09:55,553 --> 00:09:56,554
[groans]

175
00:09:56,805 --> 00:09:58,556
[panting]

176
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:02,060
What are you?

177
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:06,689
I mean, I can tell you're not a stalker,
but you don't look like a human at all.

178
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:08,650
No, of course not.

179
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:10,610
I am a Shinigami.

180
00:10:11,903 --> 00:10:15,698
Before you were captured by L,
you and I worked closely together.

181
00:10:15,865 --> 00:10:18,785
What are you talking about?
I don't understand.

182
00:10:18,868 --> 00:10:21,412
You know me? And Light is Kira?

183
00:10:22,914 --> 00:10:24,165
The Death Note...

184
00:10:24,499 --> 00:10:27,377
It grants its owner the power
to kill someone

185
00:10:27,544 --> 00:10:30,130
simply by writing
that person's name in it.

186
00:10:30,964 --> 00:10:32,590
[tires screeching]

187
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:37,929
Light Yagami took it upon himself
to punish criminals using that notebook.

188
00:10:38,221 --> 00:10:41,141
He soon became known to the world
as Kira.

189
00:10:41,266 --> 00:10:42,475
Huh...

190
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:46,396
You also possess that same power.

191
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:49,691
In fact, your ability
was even greater than his.

192
00:10:50,567 --> 00:10:52,527
You managed to find Light

193
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:56,406
by using your power to determine
that he was, in fact, Kira.

194
00:10:56,656 --> 00:11:00,243
Light is Kira, and I'm the second Kira?

195
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:03,580
[Rem] That's right.
Or rather, that used to be the case.

196
00:11:04,247 --> 00:11:06,916
Light arranged it so you would both
lose this power.

197
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:09,335
This was all according to his plan.

198
00:11:10,128 --> 00:11:12,672
He did? Then Ryuzaki was right!

199
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:17,886
Misa, do you still love Light
enough to die for him?

200
00:11:18,136 --> 00:11:19,179
[gasps]

201
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:22,390
Unbelievable.

202
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:24,184
You've gotta be telling the truth.

203
00:11:24,342 --> 00:11:26,603
You already know everything about me.

204
00:11:27,069 --> 00:11:29,528
I totally believe you now.

205
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:32,525
And, yes, I do love him.

206
00:11:32,734 --> 00:11:33,818
To death.

207
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:37,238
Not to mention how amazing it is
that Light and I were both Kira.

208
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:39,908
Of course I'd want to believe
something like that.

209
00:11:40,074 --> 00:11:42,202
I only wish I could remember it.

210
00:11:43,161 --> 00:11:45,538
You haven't changed, Misa.

211
00:11:45,872 --> 00:11:49,876
And it seems your feelings for Light
will never change either.

212
00:11:50,460 --> 00:11:52,837
It's enough to convince me
that the only way

213
00:11:52,962 --> 00:11:54,756
you can be truly happy in life,

214
00:11:54,881 --> 00:11:57,175
is if you can support him in his plan.

215
00:11:57,717 --> 00:12:00,803
-Thank you, Shinigami.
-It's Rem.

216
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:04,599
The current Kira is a vile
and pathetic human being.

217
00:12:04,766 --> 00:12:06,809
I don't know what he's capable of.

218
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:10,480
Be careful, and beware the others
from Yotsuba.

219
00:12:11,064 --> 00:12:14,484
[Rem] Trust Light. Let him do
whatever he feels necessary.

220
00:12:14,943 --> 00:12:16,110
[Misa] Okay, I got it.

221
00:12:16,236 --> 00:12:18,905
I guess I should just act normal
in the meantime, though, right?

222
00:12:19,072 --> 00:12:19,989
[Rem] That's right.

223
00:12:20,657 --> 00:12:22,283
When you go back to the interview,

224
00:12:22,367 --> 00:12:25,912
you will be able to see for yourself
who the real Kira is.

225
00:12:26,246 --> 00:12:28,623
Be on your guard and do not trust him.

226
00:12:29,582 --> 00:12:31,918
Oh my gosh, I'm so sorry I took so long.

227
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:34,462
I was just fixing up my makeup a little.

228
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:39,425
[Rem] Listen, when you return,
I will be in the room.

229
00:12:39,592 --> 00:12:42,136
The man sitting in front of me
will be Kira.

230
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:46,724
[Misa] The person in front of you is Kira.

231
00:12:56,109 --> 00:12:57,694
[Misa] Higuchi is Kira?

232
00:12:57,986 --> 00:12:59,445
That bastard.

233
00:13:18,339 --> 00:13:20,091
[Matsuda] Misa-Misa sure is late.

234
00:13:21,217 --> 00:13:22,844
[door opening]

235
00:13:23,136 --> 00:13:24,470
[Matsuda] They're back!

236
00:13:25,138 --> 00:13:26,264
Hey!

237
00:13:26,806 --> 00:13:29,642
[sighs] I'm exhausted.

238
00:13:30,351 --> 00:13:32,186
-Hey...
-How did it go?

239
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:35,273
Yotsuba agreed to hire Misa on
as their spokesperson

240
00:13:35,356 --> 00:13:36,691
for their new ad campaign.

241
00:13:37,025 --> 00:13:39,319
[L] I see. That's good to hear.

242
00:13:39,861 --> 00:13:42,363
And I made sure to give them
my cell phone number.

243
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:45,366
Would you believe three out of seven guys
already messaged me

244
00:13:45,450 --> 00:13:46,993
asking for a private date?

245
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:47,952
[Matsuda] What?

246
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:51,205
So now I accept their invitations
and investigate them, right?

247
00:13:51,414 --> 00:13:53,041
Oh, it's going exactly as I planned.

248
00:13:53,124 --> 00:13:55,043
[Light] No, the plan's
getting canceled right now.

249
00:13:55,126 --> 00:13:56,502
Huh? But why?

250
00:13:56,586 --> 00:13:58,963
Everything's been going so smoothly
up until now.

251
00:13:59,172 --> 00:14:01,674
If we go any further, you'll be in danger.

252
00:14:02,216 --> 00:14:05,595
You can still appear in their commercials
but from now on,

253
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:08,348
you should deny that you were suspected
of being the second Kira

254
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:09,807
and was detained by L.

255
00:14:10,224 --> 00:14:12,310
Mogi will continue being your bodyguard

256
00:14:12,894 --> 00:14:15,271
but you'll be working solely
as a celebrity.

257
00:14:15,438 --> 00:14:16,647
[Misa sighs]

258
00:14:17,648 --> 00:14:20,443
[Misa] If that's what you want, Light,
then that's what I'll do.

259
00:14:20,568 --> 00:14:21,444
Hmm...

260
00:14:23,613 --> 00:14:25,490
Oh well, I'm feeling pretty tired.

261
00:14:25,615 --> 00:14:28,493
Tomorrow's shoot is bright and early,
so I better get some sleep.

262
00:14:28,576 --> 00:14:29,702
[Misa giggles]

263
00:14:30,203 --> 00:14:33,289
Thank you, Light. You're so sweet
to be worried about me,

264
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:35,833
but I've thought of the best plan ever.

265
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:39,587
I'm going to be useful to you, I promise.

266
00:14:41,172 --> 00:14:42,256
[chuckles]

267
00:14:42,673 --> 00:14:45,510
[Misa] Hey, Light, want to come
sleep with me tonight?

268
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:47,178
What are you talking about?

269
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:48,846
[laughs] Just kidding.

270
00:14:49,013 --> 00:14:51,349
You're saving it
for after we catch Kira, right?

271
00:14:51,516 --> 00:14:53,434
You don't have to be shy about it.

272
00:14:54,644 --> 00:14:56,771
Yes, Light, there's no need to be shy.

273
00:14:56,938 --> 00:14:58,189
I'm not being shy.

274
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:00,608
[L] No need to be so serious either.

275
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:03,152
[director] Cut!

276
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:06,864
-Okay, that's a wrap!
-Good work, everyone.

277
00:15:07,198 --> 00:15:08,574
[all] Great job, everybody.

278
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:10,618
Great job, Misa-Misa!

279
00:15:10,785 --> 00:15:13,621
Thanks, Mochi. Can you take me
to the restroom in that hospital?

280
00:15:13,704 --> 00:15:15,665
No problem! I'll be waiting!

281
00:15:15,748 --> 00:15:16,833
TO-OH WOMEN'S MEDICAL CENTER

282
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:19,168
I'll be sure not to take too long, okay?

283
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:24,048
[Nori] Yes?

284
00:15:25,258 --> 00:15:27,135
Misa! You actually made it.

285
00:15:27,552 --> 00:15:30,680
Nori, you look so cute
in that nurse's outfit!

286
00:15:30,972 --> 00:15:32,348
[giggles] You really think so?

287
00:15:37,687 --> 00:15:39,063
TO-OH WOMEN'S MEDICAL CENTER

288
00:15:39,147 --> 00:15:40,398
Huh, that went well.

289
00:15:47,113 --> 00:15:48,364
[Misa gasps]

290
00:15:48,823 --> 00:15:50,450
What an amazing car!

291
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:52,785
If you like it,
I'll give you a ride anytime

292
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:54,370
or buy you one of your own.

293
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:57,665
By the way,
loving that nurse's outfit, Misa.

294
00:15:58,082 --> 00:15:59,876
[Misa giggles] I'm glad you like it.

295
00:16:01,878 --> 00:16:03,045
[Mogi] That took a while.

296
00:16:03,171 --> 00:16:04,088
[giggles]

297
00:16:09,177 --> 00:16:11,095
-[Mogi exclaims]
-[nervous laugh]

298
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:13,556
-Where's Misa?
-She's on a date.

299
00:16:13,681 --> 00:16:14,932
You've gotta be kidding!

300
00:16:27,445 --> 00:16:28,821
Kyosuke Higuchi…

301
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:32,950
The sleazy pervert who's been sending me
text messages ever since that party.

302
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:35,786
He's been even more persistent
than any of the other guys.

303
00:16:36,621 --> 00:16:37,788
He's Kira?

304
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:40,041
It can't get any worse than that.

305
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:42,585
-Hey, Misa?
-Huh?

306
00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:44,378
How about we grab a bite to eat?

307
00:16:45,630 --> 00:16:49,175
Are you planning to take me somewhere
and do pervy things to me?

308
00:16:49,342 --> 00:16:51,552
Well, even if you are, that's okay.

309
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:53,596
I'll be fine, since I can kill people.

310
00:16:57,099 --> 00:16:58,726
What are you saying, Misa?

311
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:00,978
Is this part of Light Yagami's plan?

312
00:17:01,145 --> 00:17:02,855
Is this what he wants you to do?

313
00:17:03,356 --> 00:17:05,107
Or is this your way of telling me

314
00:17:05,191 --> 00:17:08,694
that you want me to kill Higuchi
the moment he tries to do anything?

315
00:17:09,070 --> 00:17:10,154
[laughing]

316
00:17:10,238 --> 00:17:12,532
Come on, you're just kidding with me,
aren't you, Misa?

317
00:17:12,657 --> 00:17:14,033
You can kill people?

318
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:17,119
Yup, it's true. And you know why?

319
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:19,622
Because I'm the Second Kira.

320
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:22,542
[Higuchi] That can't be.

321
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:26,629
Even if she was the second Kira before,
there's no way she still is.

322
00:17:26,963 --> 00:17:29,131
She's not supposed to have
any memory of it either.

323
00:17:29,632 --> 00:17:30,925
What the hell's going on?

324
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:33,427
[Higuchi laughs] Misa...

325
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:36,514
You don't have to make up stuff like that
to feel safe with me.

326
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:39,141
I'm sure you'll find
that I'm quite the gentleman.

327
00:17:39,267 --> 00:17:40,768
[Misa chuckles nervously] Yeah, maybe.

328
00:17:40,977 --> 00:17:43,271
Anyway, I'll only prove
that I'm the second Kira

329
00:17:43,354 --> 00:17:44,605
to the real Kira.

330
00:17:45,022 --> 00:17:47,525
[Higuchi]
You'll only show proof to Kira? Why?

331
00:17:48,818 --> 00:17:52,321
[Misa] I'd show him because it's always
been my dream to become Kira's wife.

332
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:54,949
I know he'll need me by his side
once I tell him.

333
00:17:56,367 --> 00:17:58,578
[Higuchi]
If she really is the second Kira,

334
00:17:58,744 --> 00:18:01,038
then it's pretty clear
from the Sakura TV incident

335
00:18:01,122 --> 00:18:02,915
that she has the Shinigami eyes.

336
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:04,625
If that's the case,

337
00:18:04,709 --> 00:18:08,421
I need to make sure I keep this girl
by my side at all costs.

338
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:10,673
I've got to test her first.

339
00:18:13,092 --> 00:18:14,218
[laughs]

340
00:18:14,594 --> 00:18:18,848
Well, since I happen to be Kira,
does that mean you'll marry me?

341
00:18:21,726 --> 00:18:22,602
Hmm?

342
00:18:24,562 --> 00:18:25,605
Really?

343
00:18:26,647 --> 00:18:28,733
Yeah! I mean it.

344
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:31,110
What? Then prove it to me!

345
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:32,903
Come on, let's prove it to each other!

346
00:18:33,279 --> 00:18:34,572
I can't do that.

347
00:18:34,739 --> 00:18:38,117
It'd be a pretty bad idea
to let someone witness how I kill people.

348
00:18:38,326 --> 00:18:39,493
You think so?

349
00:18:40,161 --> 00:18:42,246
I don't know.
If I thought someone was Kira,

350
00:18:42,330 --> 00:18:44,040
I think I'd be willing to show them.

351
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:45,875
We'd never get anywhere if I didn't.

352
00:18:46,167 --> 00:18:48,544
[chuckles]
Then why don't you kill someone?

353
00:18:49,045 --> 00:18:51,088
After all, I could be the real Kira.

354
00:18:51,422 --> 00:18:54,342
Oh, all right,
but I only kill bad people, okay?

355
00:18:54,592 --> 00:18:57,136
That's right. A bad person, huh?

356
00:19:00,222 --> 00:19:02,266
This is Ginzo Kaneboshi.

357
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:04,769
President of a major finance company.

358
00:19:04,852 --> 00:19:07,229
He's infamous
for his immoral collection methods.

359
00:19:07,355 --> 00:19:10,191
Sometimes, he even makes people
pay with their insurance money.

360
00:19:10,316 --> 00:19:11,233
How about him?

361
00:19:11,317 --> 00:19:13,653
[Misa] Would you be able
to confirm his death right away?

362
00:19:13,736 --> 00:19:15,446
[Higuchi] Yeah, as soon as I call him.

363
00:19:15,529 --> 00:19:18,074
[Misa] Okay then.
Could you turn around for just a sec?

364
00:19:18,324 --> 00:19:19,617
[scribbling]

365
00:19:22,411 --> 00:19:26,707
Misa, you want me to kill Ginzo Kaneboshi,
don't you?

366
00:19:27,083 --> 00:19:30,795
Then Higuchi will believe your claim
about being the second Kira.

367
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:32,296
Very well.

368
00:19:32,421 --> 00:19:33,798
GINZO KANEBOSHI

369
00:19:34,465 --> 00:19:36,217
All right. He should be dead by now.

370
00:19:39,387 --> 00:19:40,805
Hello, this is Higuchi from Yotsuba--

371
00:19:40,888 --> 00:19:44,100
[man] Sorry, our president just collapsed
and stopped breathing! Call back later!

372
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:48,020
[man hangs up]

373
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:52,608
Told ya.

374
00:19:53,484 --> 00:19:54,944
She killed him.

375
00:19:55,736 --> 00:19:58,280
The same guy I chose just a minute ago.

376
00:19:58,698 --> 00:20:01,659
Would've been impossible to do that
unless she had the power.

377
00:20:01,951 --> 00:20:03,160
This proves it!

378
00:20:04,495 --> 00:20:05,496
[Misa gasps]

379
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:12,461
[Higuchi] So, if I'm Kira,
you'll marry me, right?

380
00:20:12,795 --> 00:20:16,674
Hey, why are you getting so serious
all of a sudden?

381
00:20:17,258 --> 00:20:20,177
-Because I'm Kira.
-Then prove it.

382
00:20:21,262 --> 00:20:23,681
I'm not gonna be able to kill
until I get home.

383
00:20:24,265 --> 00:20:25,391
You understand?

384
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:28,436
Oh, well, that's no good then.

385
00:20:29,019 --> 00:20:31,272
For all I know,
you're just making all this up

386
00:20:31,397 --> 00:20:33,607
so you have an excuse
to take me to your place.

387
00:20:33,816 --> 00:20:35,484
-Wait! I know.
-Hmm?

388
00:20:36,152 --> 00:20:39,447
Why don't you stop killing the criminals
on TV? That should prove it.

389
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:41,490
If you're Kira, it should be no problem.

390
00:20:42,116 --> 00:20:44,368
You can start killing again
when I tell you to.

391
00:20:44,452 --> 00:20:47,288
If all the times and deaths match up,
then I'll believe you.

392
00:20:47,788 --> 00:20:51,417
After all, killing criminals in that way
is something that only Kira can do.

393
00:20:52,501 --> 00:20:53,711
I see what you mean.

394
00:20:53,836 --> 00:20:54,962
That's a good idea.

395
00:20:56,367 --> 00:20:57,548
All right, Misa.

396
00:20:57,715 --> 00:21:00,050
I'm Kira, so in order
to make you trust me

397
00:21:00,176 --> 00:21:01,343
and prove that I'm him,

398
00:21:01,427 --> 00:21:03,554
I'll stop killing criminals
for the time being.

399
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:06,098
Then once you're fully convinced
I'm the real thing,

400
00:21:06,182 --> 00:21:07,725
you and I can get married.

401
00:21:07,975 --> 00:21:08,851
[all] Huh?

402
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:14,190
And so, based on what he said,
Higuchi is Kira.

403
00:21:15,691 --> 00:21:17,651
Now we not only know Kira's identity,

404
00:21:17,735 --> 00:21:20,446
but all those deaths that were worrying
the chief are gonna stop!

405
00:21:20,654 --> 00:21:22,406
That's amazing, Misa-Misa!

406
00:21:29,789 --> 00:21:36,651
TO BE CONTINUED

407
00:21:41,550 --> 00:21:47,306
[theme music plays]
